### Local testing server

- Site can be test on local server http://kz-bioprotection-php/ - it is point to public/ folder.

### Code style

- When creating styles, always check if you can use Tailwind css.
- Try to reuse existing code whenever possible and avoid creating duplicate pieces of code.
- Try to use rem for font sizes and dimensions, not specified px values. If I'm writing in pixels, convert them to rem.
- Use the global section/block spacing token `--section-spacing`, where `3.75rem` (60px) is the default vertical spacing for large screens.
- Use the shared `.section-title` class for section headers across templates. It must stay bold (`font-weight: 700`) and use `1.6667rem` on large screens (40px equivalent at 24px root size).

### text

- Make all comments in the code in English.
- Text instructions for development planning should be compiled in Russian.
- This is a multilingual site. The project must support three languages: ru - Russian, en - English and kz - Kazakh.
- Local translation files must be used only for displaying errors. All other user-facing text should come from API dictionary content.
- If the user writes a dictionary key in parentheses like `(keyBenefits)`, insert it exactly as `$dictionary['keyBenefits']` in templates, without `isset`, `is_array`, fallback values, or any other checks unless the user explicitly asks for them.

### constants

- All major global constants should be stored in a file constants/index.js
